NAME - ::<namespace>:: l2tp_stats

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

Retrieves statistics for the L2TPoX sessions configured on thespecified test port.

IxNetwork-NGPF

Retrieves statistics for the L2TPoX sessions configured on the specified test port.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::l2tp_stats

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all aggregate - Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.session - Retrieve per session l2tp statisticssession_dhcpv6pd - Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per sessionsession_dhcp_hosts - Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per sessionsession_all - Retrieve all the per session statistics

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all configured sessions or on a per session basis.Valid choices are:

Valid options are:

aggregate

Retrieve statistics for all the sessions. This is the default option.

session

Retrieve per session l2tp statistics.

tunnel

Retrieve per tunnel l2tp statistics.

session_dhcpv6pd

Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Not supported in NGPF.

session_dhcp_hosts

Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session. Not supported in NGPF.

session_all

Retrieve all the per session statistics.

DEFAULT

aggregate

-port_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The port handle for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Valid only when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port handle for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Valid only when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 None

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. The statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. The statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

-source

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Optional parameter when mode is aggregate and port_handle was provided. If specified this will represent the type of statistics to be returned. If not specified the client statistics will be tried to be retrieved and if they are empty (ie.: not lac present on the port) the server ones (LNS) will be retuned insted.

Valid options are:

client

server

DEFAULT

 None

-execution_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This is the timeout for the function. The setting is in seconds. Setting this setting to 60 it will mean that the command must complete in under 60 seconds. If the command will last more than 60 seconds the command will be terminated by force. This flag can be used to prevent dead locks occuring in IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

1800

Supported Platform Details

NAME - <namespace>::l2tp_stats

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

Retrieves statistics for the L2TPoX sessions configured on thespecified test port.

IxNetwork-NGPF

Retrieves statistics for the L2TPoX sessions configured on the specified test port.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all aggregate - Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.session - Retrieve per session l2tp statisticssession_dhcpv6pd - Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per sessionsession_dhcp_hosts - Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per sessionsession_all - Retrieve all the per session statistics

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all configured sessions or on a per session basis.Valid choices are:

Valid options are:

aggregate

Retrieve statistics for all the sessions. This is the default option.

session

Retrieve per session l2tp statistics.

tunnel

Retrieve per tunnel l2tp statistics.

session_dhcpv6pd

Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Not supported in NGPF.

session_dhcp_hosts

Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session. Not supported in NGPF.

session_all

Retrieve all the per session statistics.

DEFAULT

aggregate

port_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The port handle for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Valid only when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port handle for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Valid only when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 None

handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. The statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. The statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

source

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Optional parameter when mode is aggregate and port_handle was provided. If specified this will represent the type of statistics to be returned. If not specified the client statistics will be tried to be retrieved and if they are empty (ie.: not lac present on the port) the server ones (LNS) will be retuned insted.

Valid options are:

client

server

DEFAULT

 None

execution_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This is the timeout for the function. The setting is in seconds. Setting this setting to 60 it will mean that the command must complete in under 60 seconds. If the command will last more than 60 seconds the command will be terminated by force. This flag can be used to prevent dead locks occuring in IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

1800

NAME - <namespace>::l2tp_stats

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

Retrieves statistics for the L2TPoX sessions configured on thespecified test port.

IxNetwork-NGPF

Retrieves statistics for the L2TPoX sessions configured on the specified test port.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::l2tp_stats

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all aggregate - Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.session - Retrieve per session l2tp statisticssession_dhcpv6pd - Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per sessionsession_dhcp_hosts - Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per sessionsession_all - Retrieve all the per session statistics

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all configured sessions or on a per session basis.Valid choices are:

Valid options are:

aggregate

Retrieve statistics for all the sessions. This is the default option.

session

Retrieve per session l2tp statistics.

tunnel

Retrieve per tunnel l2tp statistics.

session_dhcpv6pd

Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Not supported in NGPF.

session_dhcp_hosts

Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session. Not supported in NGPF.

session_all

Retrieve all the per session statistics.

DEFAULT

aggregate

port_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The port handle for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Valid only when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port handle for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Valid only when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 None

handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. The statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the L2TPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. The statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

source

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Optional parameter when mode is aggregate and port_handle was provided. If specified this will represent the type of statistics to be returned. If not specified the client statistics will be tried to be retrieved and if they are empty (ie.: not lac present on the port) the server ones (LNS) will be retuned insted.

Valid options are:

client

server

DEFAULT

 None

execution_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This is the timeout for the function. The setting is in seconds. Setting this setting to 60 it will mean that the command must complete in under 60 seconds. If the command will last more than 60 seconds the command will be terminated by force. This flag can be used to prevent dead locks occuring in IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

1800

Supported Platform Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

status
